{"atom_id": "md_dmTV_ex_a031", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TV/examples.md", "line_start": 64, "line_end": 64, "parent_section": "§TV.2 [Trial Visits Issues]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "### Identifying Trial Visits", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.4", "ts": "2026-05-11T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmTV_ex_a032", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TV/examples.md", "line_start": 66, "line_end": 66, "parent_section": "§TV.2.1 [Identifying Trial Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In general, a trial's visits are defined in its protocol.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.4", "ts": "2026-05-11T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmTV_ex_a033", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TV/examples.md", "line_start": 66, "line_end": 66, "parent_section": "§TV.2.1 [Identifying Trial Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The term \"visit\" reflects the fact that data in outpatient studies is usually collected during a physical visit by the subject to a clinic.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.4", "ts": "2026-05-11T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmTV_ex_a034", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TV/examples.md", "line_start": 66, "line_end": 66, "parent_section": "§TV.2.1 [Identifying Trial Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sometimes a trial visit defined by the protocol may not correspond to a physical visit.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.4", "ts": "2026-05-11T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmTV_ex_a035", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TV/examples.md", "line_start": 66, "line_end": 66, "parent_section": "§TV.2.1 [Identifying Trial Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "It may span multiple physical visits, as when screening data is collected over several clinic visits but recorded under one TV name (VISIT) and number (VISITNUM).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.4", "ts": "2026-05-11T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmTV_ex_a036", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TV/examples.md", "line_start": 66, "line_end": 66, "parent_section": "§TV.2.1 [Identifying Trial Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A trial visit may represent only a portion of an extended physical visit, as when a trial of in-patients collects data under multiple trial visits for a single hospital admission.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.4", "ts": "2026-05-11T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmTV_ex_a037", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TV/examples.md", "line_start": 68, "line_end": 68, "parent_section": "§TV.2 [Trial Visits Issues]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "### Trial Visit Rules", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.4", "ts": "2026-05-11T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmTV_ex_a038", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TV/examples.md", "line_start": 70, "line_end": 70, "parent_section": "§TV.2.2 [Trial Visit Rules]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Visit start rules are different from element start rules in that they usually describe when a visit should occur; element start rules describe the moment at which an element is considered to start.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.4", "ts": "2026-05-11T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmTV_ex_a039", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TV/examples.md", "line_start": 70, "line_end": 70, "parent_section": "§TV.2.2 [Trial Visit Rules]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "There are usually gaps between visits, periods of time that do not belong to any visit, so it is usually not necessary to identify the moment when one visit stops and another starts.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.4", "ts": "2026-05-11T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmTV_ex_a040", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TV/examples.md", "line_start": 72, "line_end": 72, "parent_section": "§TV.2.2 [Trial Visit Rules]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Visit start rules are usually expressed relative to the start or end of an element or epoch (e.g., \"1-2 hours before end of First Wash-out\", \"8 weeks after end of 2nd Treatment Epoch\").", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.4", "ts": "2026-05-11T08:00:00Z"}}
